{{italic title}}
'''''Covert Warfare:  Intelligence, Counterintelligence and Military Deception During the World War II Era''''' is an eighteen volume book edited by [[John Mendelsohn (historian)|John Mendelsohn]] and published in 1989 by [[Garland]].
The series contains [[Sanitization (classified information)|sanitized]] versions of selected previously [[classified document]]s from the [[National Archives]] record groups.

* [[Library of Congress Classification]]: D810.S7 (D810S7C66)
* [[Dewey Decimal Classification]]: 940.5485

