{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2012}}
'''''Description of Kingdom of Georgia''''' was written by [[Vakhushti|Vakhushti Bagrationi]]. The full name of the work is "''Description of Kingdom of Georgia, its habits and canons''" ({{lang-ka|აღწერა სამეფოსა საქართველოსა, ზნენი და ჩვეულებანი საქართველოსანი}}). The work was completed on 20 October 1745 in [[Moscow]]. The work thoroughly describes the [[Geography of Georgia (country)|geography of Georgia]], its [[Administrative divisions of Georgia (country)|regions]] and peoples, and narrates the [[History of Georgia (country)|history of Georgia]] from its origin to the first half of the 18th century. The work was inscribed on [[UNESCO]]'s [[Memory of the World Register]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=''Description of Georgian Kingdom''<!-- sic --> and the Geographical Atlas of Vakhushti Bagrationi|url=http://www.unesco.org/new/en/communication-and-information/flagship-project-activities/memory-of-the-world/register/full-list-of-registered-heritage/registered-heritage-page-2/description-of-georgian-kingdom-and-the-geographical-atlas-of-vakhushti-bagrationi/| work=Memory of the World Register|publisher=UNESCO|accessdate=17 April 2017}}</ref>

