{{Infobox Museum | name = Long Museum | logo = Long_Museum_Logo.jpg | location = [[Shanghai]] | publictransit = [[Middle Longhua Road Station|Middle Longhua Road]] {{rint|shanghai|7}} |website = [http://www.thelongmuseum.org/en/ www.longmusem.org] }} [[File:CONTINUOUS 2012 Coll. Long Museum West Bund - Shanghai - China WEB.jpg|thumb|upright|'CONTINUOUS' 2012 by [[Bert van Loo]] (Long Museum West Bund)]]
The '''Long Museum''' ({{zh|s=龙美术馆|l=Dragon Art Museum}}) is a private [[art museum]] in [[Shanghai]], [[China]], founded by [[Liu Yiqian]] and his wife Wang Wei. The museum has two locations in Shanghai: the Long Museum [[Pudong]] and Long Museum West Bund.<ref name="about">Long Museum website: [http://thelongmuseum.org/en/page/detailed/038do About Long Museum]</ref>
In 2016, a third location was opened in Chongqing and a Wuhan branch is scheduled for 2018.<ref name=newyorker>{{cite web |url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2016/11/07/the-emperors-new-museum|title= THE EMPEROR’S NEW MUSEUM|last1= Jiayang |first1=Fan |date= November 7, 2016 |website=Newyorker.com |publisher=New Yorker |accessdate= November 7, 2016}}</ref>
==History== The Long Museum Pudong was officially opened to the public on December 18, 2012.<ref name="about"/> The Long Museum West Bund opened on March 28, 2014 and was China's largest private museum at the time of its opening.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://artradarjournal.com/2014/04/04/chinas-largest-private-art-museum-opens-on-shanghais-west-bund/|title= China's largest private art museum opens on Shanghai's West Bund|last1=Naji |first1=Cassandra |date=4 April 2014 |website=Art Radar |publisher= |accessdate=27 November 2014}}</ref>It is the second of Chinese billionaire collectors Liu Yiqian and Wang Wei's expanding empire. The architecture was designed by Liu Yichun of Atelier Deshaus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smartshanghai.com/venue/11133/long_museum_west_bund|title=Long Museum (West Bund) {{!}} SmartShanghai|website=www.smartshanghai.com|language=en|access-date=2018-04-19}}</ref>
==See also== * [[West Bund]] * [[50 Moganshan Road]] * [[China Art Museum]] * [[Museum of Contemporary Art Shanghai]] * [[Shanghai Museum]] * [[Tianzifang]] * [[Xintiandi]] * [[798 Art Zone]]
