[[Image:Alay Köşkü (2).JPG|thumb|Procession Kiosk, across the [[Sublime Porte]] (left).]]
The '''Procession Kiosk''' ({{lang-tr|Alay Köşkü}}) is a 16th-century historical building on the outer walls of the [[Gülhane Park]] next to [[Topkapı Palace]] in [[Istanbul, Turkey]]. It was used by the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] sultans to receive the salute of processing [[janissary]] as well as a pleasure locale. The building is situated across the [[Sublime Porte]].

In 2011, the building was transferred to the [[Ahmet Hamdi Tanpınar Literature Museum Library]] .<ref name="hdn1"/>

